==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indeterminable
<hw>In`de*ter"mi*na*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indeterminabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ind⟦eacute⟧terminable</ets>.
See <er>In-</er> not, and Determine.]</ety> <def>Not determinable;
impossible to be determined; not to be definitely known, ascertained,
defined, or limited.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>In`de*ter"mi*na*bly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indeterminable</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Indeterminable
<hw>In`de*ter"mi*na*ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An indeterminable thing
or quantity.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indeterminate</ent>⟦br⟧
